commitResults.messageTitle: Remove Duke.java and Add Jeeves.java
commitResults.messageBody: Change the name and personality of the chatbot.

commitResults.messageTitle: Jeeves class, main method: Update to be responsive to user input
commitResults.messageBody:
The program only starts and ends instantly.

There is a need for it to be able to recognize user input and respond accordingly.

Let's add the ability to read and recognize user input.
Specifically, Jeeves can recognize the 'bye' command and terminate appropriately.
All other commands will simply be echoed back.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Task.java
commitResults.messageBody:
No program logic exists for managing tasks.

A Task Object will allow for the management of tasks cleanly.

Let's add the Task class with a default constructor and getter/setters.

Merge branch 'branch-Level-10'
Fix bugs related to GUI commit
commitResults.messageBody:
There were several error messages that were not being displayed on the
GUI by Jeeves.

Not having those messages be displayed to the user greatly affects user
experience as they would not have any clue what or if anything was wrong
at all.

Let's update the code such that all error messages are properly shown
by Jeeves and no part of the code attempts to print to a command line
output.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions to multiple classes
commitResults.messageBody:
The program assumes that perfect input/output will be received at
several points.

This can lead to unhandled crashes if there is a developer mistake.

Let's add assertions to the program so such that cases can be
specifically detected at run time.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'master' into A-CodeQuality
Improve overall code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
The code violates several of the recommended code quality principals
as suggested by the textbook.

Let's update the code to remove or minimize the instances of these
violations.
* Long methods
* Deep Nesting
* Magic Literals
* Multiple levels of abstraction
